HEADWORD: Marmoratum opus
<hw>Mar`mo*ra`tum o"pus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L. See
<er>Marmorate</er>, and <er>Opus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A
kind of hard finish for plasterwork, made of plaster of Paris and marble
dust, and capable of taking a high polish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

